American foulbrood of honey bees, Netherlands
----------------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 29 Aug 2014 from Dr Christianne Bruschke, Chief Veterinary Officer, Ministry of Economic Affairs, Ministry of Economic Affairs, The Hague, Netherlands

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 21 Aug 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 27 Aug 2014
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2008
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Paenibacillus larvae_
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Zuidlaren, Drenthe
Date of start of the outbreak: 21 Aug 2014
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: apiary
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Bees (hives) / 14 / 1 / - / 1 / -

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Bees (hives) / 7.14 percent / ** / ** / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comment: A 3 km [2 mi] perimeter has been established around the outbreak.

Control measures
Measures applied: stamping out; movement control inside the country; screening; zoning; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Central Veterinarian Institute, Lelystad (national laboratory) / Bees/ pathogenic agent isolation on culture / 27 Aug 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

