[For background information on American foulbrood (AFB) see ProMED-mail report 20130930.1976297.

In 2008, 2 outbreaks were reported by the Netherlands. The information available in its annual report indicated that these outbreaks occurred between September and October 2008. The location of these outbreaks was not available. See annual report at http://tinyurl.com/lc5khs3.

The condition is also present in Germany where in 2013, 95 outbreaks were reported. See annual report 2013 at http://tinyurl.com/pykl6zf (Note: go to Section 3 of the report named "Detailed quantitative information for OIE-listed diseases/infections present" to see detailed information on these outbreaks).

In addition, Belgium reported an occurrence of AFB in September 2013 and to date, 25 outbreaks have been reported. See event summary and updated map at http://tinyurl.com/lpchczy.

Given the worldwide decline in bee populations, the OIE has dedicated its latest Bulletin to this issue (Bulletin no. 2 2014 "Protecting bees, preserving our future". This bulletin is available at http://tinyurl.com/lv2ly6o. - Mod.CRD

Maps of the Netherlands can be seen at http://www.map-of-netherlands.co.uk/images/netherlands-politcal-map.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2735368,23423. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
